  "local_port": 49240,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure of getting admission into IIT for NRIs?",
  "response": "Admission to the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) for Non-Resident Indians (NRIs) can be pursued mainly through two primary channels: the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) Advanced and the Direct Admission of Students Abroad (DASA) scheme. Here are the procedures for each:\n\n### Through JEE Advanced\n\n1. **Eligibility:**\n   - NRIs must meet all eligibility criteria, similar to resident Indian students.\n   - Must have completed or be appearing for the class 12th examination with Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics as subjects.\n   - Age criteria: Born on or after October 1, 1998 (for specific admission year, as the criteria may change annually).\n\n2. **JEE Examination Process:**\n   - **JEE Main:** Foreign nationals, including NRIs, must first appear for the JEE Main, which serves as a qualifying exam for the JEE Advanced.\n   - **JEE Advanced:** Top candidates from JEE Main are eligible to appear for the JEE Advanced. Clearing this test is a prerequisite for admission to undergraduate programs.\n\n3. **Application Process:**\n   - Registration for JEE Main and JEE Advanced is typically online via the official exam portals.\n   - Ensure all necessary documents (passport, academic transcripts) are available.\n\n4. **Counseling and Admission:**\n   - Successful candidates from JEE Advanced participate in the Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) counseling process to secure a seat in an IIT.\n\n### Through DASA Scheme\n\nThis pathway is less common for IITs specifically, as it is more prevalent for other technical institutions such as NITs or IIITs, and other central government-funded technical institutes. However, eligibility and process details for DASA are as follows:\n\n1. **Eligibility:**\n   - Must have completed the qualifying examination outside India, or must be an NRI.\n   - Must qualify SAT Subject Tests (also known as SAT II) in Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics Level 2.\n\n2. **DASA Application Process:**\n   - Submit an online application through the DASA portal.\n   - Submit SAT Subject Test scores, along with other required documentation like academic transcripts and passport details.\n\n3. **Admission Process:**\n   - Admission is based on the scores in the SAT Subject Tests.\n   - Merit lists are published, and successful candidates proceed with the seat allocation process.\n\nIt's essential to check the latest details from the official websites for JEE and DASA, as admission procedures, eligibility criteria, and important dates may change. Additionally, specific details can vary each year based on updates from the Ministry of Education and associated bodies.",
